Download Kali Linux VM
Head to the official Kali Linux website: Get Kali Linux.
Download the Kali Linux VirtualBox Image (if using VirtualBox) or the VMware Image (if using VMware).
ðŸ’¡ Tip: Choose the image that matches your virtualization software for a smoother setup process.

Set Up the Virtual Machine
Oracle VirtualBox (Recommended) or VMware can be used.
In VirtualBox:
Open VirtualBox and click on File â†’ Import Appliance.
Select the Kali Linux .ova file you downloaded.
Click Next, review the settings, and click Import.

Start and Install Kali Linux
Once imported, select the Kali VM and click Start.
Follow the on-screen prompts to complete the Kali Linux installation.

Log In to Kali Linux
After installation, log in using the default credentials:
Username: kali
Password: kali
